      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of clinically relevant loading scenarios or match the intended COU loading precisely.",
      "rationale": "Testing conducted at a single load configuration (ASTM F1717 standard geometry, 70 mm offset, quasi-static 5 mm/min displacement rate). No variation in offset distance, rod diameter, or loading rate was explored. Achieved level 2 falls below required level 3; this factor is noted as a gap in the credibility assessment and is accepted on the basis that the standard test condition represents the worst-case bending moment for this construct geometry."
    },
    {
